         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Immediate ¶ Chief Secretary's Office, ¶ Melbourne, ¶ 31 August ¶ 18 ¶ 71 ¶ Sir, ¶ I have the honor by direction of the Chief Secretary to request that you will be good enough to furnish this Departmen...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.08.31</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Y71/11274, unit 576, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">Immediate</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">Chief Secretary's Office,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">Melbourne,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>31 August<seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>18</seg>71</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">Sir,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor by direction of the Chief Secretary to request that you will be good enough to furnish this Department</seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">, at as early a date as possible,</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; color: #2F5496; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Underlining has been added under 'at as early a date as possible'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with</seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the undermentioned<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Returns<seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">, for the purpose of being laid before the Legislative<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Assembly<seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">, in compliance with an<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Order<seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on the motion of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Mr.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mason M.P<seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In a Legislative Assembly debate on Supply on 23 August<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1871,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mason stated 'Seventy-seven days ago<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he (Mr. Mason) moved for a return relative<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to officers of the civil service provided<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with quarters in addition to salary, but the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>order had not yet been fully complied with'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>A part return had been provided on 8 August.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The text of the order 'Allowance of quarters to Civil Servants', made on 7 June 1871,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>listed the details given in the manuscript post-script to the memorandum.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The Chief Secretary, C. Gavan Duffy, presented a return to the Legislative assembly on 18 October<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Victoria<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Parliamentary debates</seg>, session 1871, pp. 481,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>782,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>969<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and 1583). Copies of the returns have not been found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">I have the honor to be,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient Servant</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>W. H. Odgers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The Director Botanic Gardens</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">1. The number, name and official position of civil servants and other officers employed by the Government who, in addition to salary, are provided with quarters, or receive an extra allowance for house rent, fuel, light, or other necessities.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">2. The estimated annual rateable value of all such quarters, the value of each separate tenement to specifically given.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">3. The number, name, and official position of officers and servants employed by the Government who, in addition to fixed salary, are authorized or allowed to receive and retain fees, premiums, or other payments, in the discharge of their official duties or otherwise.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No response by M has been found.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
